00:35:18.140 --> 00:35:19.170
DR. MARC SCHOEN:
Great question.

00:35:19.170 --> 00:35:20.590
Excellent question.

00:35:20.590 --> 00:35:24.010
And because I've had limited
time, I couldn't expand on it.

00:35:24.010 --> 00:35:25.280
But you're absolutely right.

00:35:25.280 --> 00:35:28.680
The goal isn't just to
create agitation.

00:35:28.680 --> 00:35:32.020
The goal is to change
how we label, how we

00:35:32.020 --> 00:35:33.760
experience that agitation.

00:35:33.760 --> 00:35:37.160
There's actually a part in the
brain that straddles the old

00:35:37.160 --> 00:35:38.290
and new brain.

00:35:38.290 --> 00:35:41.470
And its job is to interpret our

00:35:41.470 --> 00:35:43.980
physical experience inside.

00:35:43.980 --> 00:35:48.680
Because the physiology of being
stressed out and fearful

00:35:48.680 --> 00:35:51.920
is not necessarily different
than the physiology of being

00:35:51.920 --> 00:35:53.590
happy and excited.

00:35:53.590 --> 00:35:55.730
But there's a part of the brain
that interprets that

00:35:55.730 --> 00:36:00.100
physiology as bad or
as OK or good.

00:36:00.100 --> 00:36:05.900
So what we want to do is train
ourselves that this type of

00:36:05.900 --> 00:36:10.150
discomfort actually
is beneficial.

00:36:10.150 --> 00:36:14.480
Now, the elaborate way in my
writings, I show that what we

00:36:14.480 --> 00:36:19.450
can do is take this kind of
agitation and recondition the

00:36:19.450 --> 00:36:22.440
brain to react differently.

00:36:22.440 --> 00:36:26.800
And one way actually is to
use a social component.

00:36:26.800 --> 00:36:31.340
One very fascinating way which I
use in my classes is to take

00:36:31.340 --> 00:36:35.720
this, create an agitation,
create a stress, but do it in

00:36:35.720 --> 00:36:38.050
a group of people.

00:36:38.050 --> 00:36:41.280
So now, first of all, there's
pressure to perform

00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:44.210
in a group of people.

00:36:44.210 --> 00:36:47.770
And it creates a vulnerability,
because you

00:36:47.770 --> 00:36:53.060
know you're going to either fail
or succeed in your peers.

00:36:53.060 --> 00:36:57.830
But the group process actually
stimulates our

00:36:57.830 --> 00:37:00.630
hormones in the body.

00:37:00.630 --> 00:37:02.610
A thing called oxytocin.

00:37:02.610 --> 00:37:03.620
You've probably heard of it.

00:37:03.620 --> 00:37:05.620
It's this good feeling
hormone.

00:37:05.620 --> 00:37:07.955
And so what happens
is-- it happens to

00:37:07.955 --> 00:37:10.180
both men and women--

00:37:10.180 --> 00:37:13.270
is that now they're in a
vulnerable situation, feeling

00:37:13.270 --> 00:37:15.830
pressure, in this
group situation,

00:37:15.830 --> 00:37:17.500
which creates a bonding.

00:37:17.500 --> 00:37:20.440
These hormones are released
in the body.

00:37:20.440 --> 00:37:27.090
And so now it gets associated
in the brain with a warmer,

00:37:27.090 --> 00:37:29.450
positive, connected feeling.

00:37:29.450 --> 00:37:32.230
So we're teaching you that
of vulnerability, of

00:37:32.230 --> 00:37:36.080
transparency, rather than of
perfection, being uptight,

00:37:36.080 --> 00:37:40.370
being angry, being fearful,
that a transparency of

00:37:40.370 --> 00:37:44.510
vulnerability actually creates
a good feeling.

00:37:44.510 --> 00:37:45.780
That's how we start doing it.

00:37:45.780 --> 00:37:47.130
